INTRODUCTION
-> JavaScript is a lightweight, cross-platform and interpreted scripting language.
-> It can be used for both CLient-side as well as Server-side Scripting.
-> Javascirpt is used to make our webpage more lively and interactive.
-> The main advantage of JavaScript is that all modern web browsers support JavaScript.
-> Also, JavaScript runs on any operating system.

VARIABLES AND DATATYPES
-> Allows us to work with the following primitive data types:
    1. Number : floating point number, for decimals and integers
    2. Strings : sequence of charactrers used for text
    3. Boolean : logical data type - takes only true and false
    4. null : non-existent 
    5. undefined : variable that doesn't have a value yet
-> 'var' keyword to define the variable.
-> JS has dynamic typing : data tyoes are automatically assigned to the variables.
-> variable names can not start with numbers or symbols except 'underscore(_)' and 'dollar($)'.
-> must start with letter.
-> can not use reserved keywords as variable names.

OPERATORS
-> makes use of different kinds of operators.
-> They include : 
    1. Arithmetic
    2. Logical
    3. Comparison
    4. Assignment
    5. Conditional, etc.
    
typeof Operator
-> The typeof operator is a unary operator that is placed before its single operand, which can be of any type. Its value is a string indicating the data type of the operand.
-> The typeof operator evaluates to "number", "string", or "boolean" if its operand is a number, string, or boolean value and returns true or false based on the evaluation.
